The paper discusses a system for securing legacy applications running on ARM-based processors, which involves partitioning resources into secure and normal worlds using ARM TrustZone technology. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of computer security (cs.CR), operating systems (cs.OS), software engineering (cs.SE), systems and control (cs.SY), or architecture (cs.AR). However, given the focus on security and the use of TrustZone technology, cs.CR and cs.OS are the most likely categories.
